        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-06-05 18:10:56.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-2\n\nThe root pom should not be listed as a dependency of sdnc-core top level pom, since that would create a circular dependency (sdnc-core/pom.xml has sdnc-core/rootpom.xml as its parent).\n\nThe missing 1.1.0 version seems to be related to problems we have been having with the Nexus staging plugin (that version existed at one point, but has disappeared).  As a fix, I'm submitting a change to the root pom to set its version back to 1.1.0, followed by a separate change to roll the root pom version to 1.1.2, and then finally changes to all the sdnc- repos to use version 1.1.2 of the root pom.  This way we can avoid the issue of an older 1.1.0 version being picked up from the staging repo (which is the issue we have been seeing)",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
